text: Kazayak () is a rural locality (a selo) in Krasnovoskhodsky Selsoviet, Iglinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 878 as of 2010. There are 14 streets. == Geography == It is located 93 km from Iglino, 8 km from Krasny Voskhod. == References == Category:Rural localities in Iglinsky District
title: Kazayak
